{"word":"H3442 - יֵשׁוּעַ - Yêshûwaʻ - yay-shoo'-ah - Jeshua","slug":"H3442","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יֵשׁוּעַ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Yêshûwaʻ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yay-shoo'-ah"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Jeshua"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>ישׁוּע</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>yêshûa‛</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>yay-shoo'-ah</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Jeshua = \"he is saved\" <ol><li>son of Nun of the tribe of Ephraim and successor to Moses as the leader of the children of Israel; led the conquest of Canaan (noun proper masculine)</li><li>son of Jehozadak and high priest after the restoration (noun proper masculine)</li><li>a priest in the time of David who had charge of the 9th course (noun proper masculine)</li><li>a Levite in the reign of Hezekiah (noun proper masculine)</li><li>head of a Levitical house which returned from captivity in Babylon (noun proper masculine)</li><li>father of a builder of the wall of Jerusalem in the time of Nehemiah (noun proper masculine)</li><li>a town in southern Judah reinhabited by the people of Judah after the return from captivity (noun proper locative)</li></ol> <p />Origin: for <a href=\"#/H3091\">H3091</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1933\">H1933</a>, <a href=\"#/H1942\">H1942</a>, <a href=\"#/H1943\">H1943</a>, <a href=\"#/H1944\">H1944</a>, <a href=\"#/H1953\">H1953</a>, <a href=\"#/H1962\">H1962</a>, <a href=\"#/H3050\">H3050</a>, <a href=\"#/H3058\">H3058</a>, <a href=\"#/H3059\">H3059</a>, <a href=\"#/H3060\">H3060</a>, <a href=\"#/H3068\">H3068</a>, <a href=\"#/H3069\">H3069</a>, <a href=\"#/H3075\">H3075</a>, <a href=\"#/H3076\">H3076</a>, <a href=\"#/H3077\">H3077</a>, <a href=\"#/H3078\">H3078</a>, <a href=\"#/H3079\">H3079</a>, <a h